title: For Sale:  Armalite AR-30 300WM Long Range Sniper Rifle
location: Palmetto Bay / Pinecrest, Miami-Dade, South Florida
postcontent:
This bolt action, magazine fed, Armalite AR-30 rifle is chambered in .300 Win Mag.  The rifle is built like a .50 Caliber BMG.  The Winchester Magnum round is known for high muzzle velocities and a flat bullet trajectory. This is a great gun to reach out well beyond 1000 yards.  It has a 26" barrel.  It is right handed.  I have upgraded the pistol grip to a Magpul - I didn't care for the factory grip.  It has the OEM scope base installed.  I have (2) 5 round magazines - it came with one and the other cost ~$80.  The muzzle brake is very efficient.  The gun is in good shape.  It has a couple of small safe marks - I can send pictures if requested.

If you want to shoot long range, this is a great gun for it.  The 300WM round is nearly twice the size of a standard 308 round.  The 300 Win Mag rounds are typically less than $2/round - not $5-10/round like 338 Lapua and 50 BMG.  You wil have the same accuracy, and can shoot all day at the discounted ammo price.  If you haven't checked it out yet, the new Long Shot Range will be a great place to visit with this rifle.

I am asking $1800 OBRO for the rifle, scope base and magazines.  I will throw in the $100 Harris bipod for $60.  Total package price is $1860 - a smokin deal for a ready to go package for shooting long range. A new one with no accessories, no scope rail and one magazine is $3400.  This i half price!

Please reach out to me with any questions or reasonable offers.  Thanks for looking!

FYI - there is no scope - I took my US Optics off and will be keeping it.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1966 Ford Thunderbird
postcontent:
Hello,

I am relocating to Montana for work on short notice. As such, I am forced to sell my T-bird, as I will not have room for it where I am headed. 

The car is pretty much a factory original 390 4-barrel A/C car. 

Pretty much meaning I've replaced the front ball joints(01/13), tires (02/13), re-cored and replaced the radiator (04/14), and the previous owner removed the A/C compressor and lost it.

It has one minor issue, that causes a major problem, that being a pinhole leak in the expansion tank. A new one can be found at the link below. I tried to fix it last weekend before I had to leave town while I was installing the radiator but ran out of time. The tank can be repaired, for probably less than $100.00 if you were to take it to a shop, and probably for less than $50.00 if you were to do it yourself. The major problem caused by the leak of course is that you can't hold coolant for long in the pressurized tank.
http://www.macsautoparts.com/ford_thunderbird/ford-thunderbird-expansion-tank-filler-neck-on-left-side-1965-66.html

Aside from that issue, the car starts on the first turn of the key every time, and it runs like a champ. It has power windows, door locks, seats, and steering. The original AM radio, and sequential turn signals that work perfectly. Paint and chrome are in pretty good condition too. It's been a FUN daily driver, and city cruiser, it gets thumbs ups and cheers from people on the road all the time. I will miss it. 

You can see for yourself, the car's value ranges from $5,300 to $12,000 as a base model; however, with the engine being the 390/335 HP V8 Engine 4 barrel model, it gets a value bump of 30%, to a range of $6,900-$16,700. 
http://www.nadaguides.com/Classic-Cars/1966/Ford/Thunderbird/2-Door-Hardtop/Values

If you were to replace the missing A/C parts overall value goes up another 10%.
http://www.nadaguides.com/Classic-Cars/1966/Ford/Thunderbird/2-Door-Hardtop/Values

All that being said, needing to sell it, and understanding that it needs some work to get it back on the road properly, I am willing to take around $7,500, I'm also willing to accept reasonable cash + trade offers. The title is clean, from NV, and a bill of sale will be provided at the sale. 

Let me know if you have any questions or fair offers.

This is a High Powered Rifle that has been modified to meet Indiana specs and requirements . This rifle is 100 % legal to hunt with in Indiana .
Don’t wait for Deer season to decide you want one, you won’t be able to. This is someone’s chance to own
a very nice Indiana Deer Legal High Powered Rifle of which only a hand full are available.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1600 with scope or $1400 without.This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR

This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
